# Memory Forensics - TryHackMe Notes

## Introduction to Memory Forensics

Memory Forensics is the process of analyzing a computer’s RAM (Random Access Memory) to investigate malicious activities, running processes, network connections, passwords, malware, and other evidence that may not exist on the disk.

RAM contains:

* Running processes
* Active network connections
* Logged-in users
* Encryption keys
* Clipboard data
* Command history
* Malware running in memory

Memory forensics is important because attackers often use fileless malware and in-memory attacks.

# Common Memory File Extensions

| Extension | Description        |
| --------- | ------------------ |
| .mem      | Raw memory dump    |
| .raw      | Raw memory image   |
| .dmp      | Memory dump        |
| .img      | Memory image       |
| .bin      | Binary memory file |

